title: Man Stops Arson Suspect From Throwing 2nd Molotov Cocktail
description: A man tried to stop an alleged arsonist by knocking a molotov cocktail out of the suspect’s hand after he allegedly set fire to a deli. The terrifying scene took place in Brooklyn, New York. The FDNY released video of the incident. One camera caught the suspect outside the deli igniting the explosive device before throwing it inside the store. Video from inside shows how the bottle exploded and quickly engulfed the store in flames. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

title: Why Are People Vandalizing Teslas?
description: Teslas may be the “it” car for the tech forward and environmentally friendly, but they’re also the target of an outsized number of vandalism attacks. These acts of vandalism cost car owners thousands of dollars, but the cameras may help identify the perpetrators. #InsideEdition

title: Dramatic smash-and-grab robbery at west London jewellers is caught on CCTV
description:
CCTV captures the shocking moment thieves drive a Range Rover into the front of a west London jewellers before they rob the shop and attempt to flee. The incident happened in front of shocked customers at the store in Shepherds Bush last October. The three individuals used hammers to smash glass display cabinets before stuffing the jewels into bags and pockets. One of the robbers was caught and detained by members of the public before police arrived and arrested him. He is now serving a 10-year jail sentence after pleading guilty to robbery, dangerous driving, and possession of offensive weapon, criminal damage and receiving stolen goods.

title: Pune Car Accident | Weeks After Porsche Horror, Car Flings Woman Into Air Near Pune
description:
A woman was seriously injured after being hit by a speeding Wagon-R car in Pimpri Chinchwad city of Maharashtra. The video of the accident shows her being tossed into air and fly at least 10 feet and land hard on the road. The incident is said to have taken place on June 12 at Swaraj Chowk. The woman was later taken to the hospital by the driver, the police said. "After the accident, the injured woman was treated at a private hospital by the driver himself," said Shivaji Pawar, a senior officer of the local police.
